history.content: I think it depends on how much time you're currently spending on the class, and how comfortable you feel with circuits versus linear algebra. I spent probably double the amount of time on the class during the circuits module compared to the linalg one, and I had similar amounts of experience with each going into the class. So consider the future workload as well.

I'm taking 162 and 16A, pretty involved in a few extra-curriculars and trying to recruit for this summer.

I've done the last two 16A homeworks last minute and I'll probably be doing the same for the third...I think this could get slightly better as the semester continues.

I'm currently a junior CS major and, if I were to stick with my current schedule, I'd have 3 upper division CS courses left to graduate for senior year. Should I drop 16A and just take 2 major courses each semester during senior year, or should I stick with it? Can't drop 162 anymore so that's out of the question.

Thanks!
history.subject: Should I drop EE 16A?
